    "narrative": "The slate for Ghost Ride the WHIP is headlined by **Corbin Carroll**, who registers an elite 87.14 efficiency score against M\u00e1rquez. This is the premier play of the day, driven by an exploitable 5.26 xERA from the opposition and a significant stolen base opportunity against a pitcher with a lethargic delivery (86% SB success rate), which is critical for our focus on speed. Similarly, **Seiya Suzuki** (68.49) and **Brice Turang** (63.94) provide high-floor production. **Seiya Suzuki** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost against Sasaki, while **Brice Turang**\u2019s leadoff positioning and the favorable matchup against Keller propel him into our \"Strong\" start tier, despite the presence of a tough catcher behind the plate.\n\nRegarding bench decisions, **Max Muncy** (50.89) was the most difficult exclusion, narrowly edged out by the superior matchup context surrounding **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Alex Freeland**. While **Max Muncy** offers reasonable platoon value, the optimizer prioritized the volume and situational efficiency of our current starters. We are monitoring the status of **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Giancarlo Stanton**, both of whom are confirmed pending lineup verification; we have assumed them in the #6 and #5 spots respectively, but their final slotting could adjust these projections slightly. Investors should note the \ud83d\udea8 RAINOUT for **Mickey Moniak**, ensuring his removal from all daily calculations. While **Austin Riley** remains on the pine, his 44.19 score against Wheeler\u2019s elite 2.73 xERA makes him an easy fade today given the depth of our middle infield options like **Brice Turang** and the relative scarcity of stolen base contributors currently in the active rotation.",
